# API routes

## Base path

Effective URLs are `/<ApiPrefix>/{controller-template}/...` when a route prefix convention prepends `<ApiPrefix>` for API controllers.

## Controller templates

Use plural, lowercase route segments that match the resource:

- `[Route("users")]`, `[Route("roles")]`, `[Route("companies")]`, `[Route("resources")]`, `[Route("auth")]`.

## Actions

- Standard CRUD: `[HttpGet]`, `[HttpGet("{id:int}")]`, `[HttpPost]`, `[HttpPut("{id:int}")]`, `[HttpDelete("{id:int}")]`.
- Multi-word paths use kebab-case: `refresh-token`, `reset-password`, `mass-insert`, nested like `{id:int}/reset-password/send-email`.

## Full API catalog

Do not duplicate full route tables in rules. Use Swagger in Development as the source of truth.
